Color. Carapace (
Fig. 10
) yellow brown. Cervical groove, radial furrows and median furrow gray black, anterior median part between cervical grooves gray black. Eyes with black ring. Chelicerae and sternum yellow brown. Endites yellow brown, gray distally. Labium brown. Legs yellow brown, reddish-brown on femora I. Dorsum of opisthosoma gray yellow, with thin, ripple-shaped lateral striates, covered with some white patches, median stripe dark and posterior margin with several dispersive gray black patches; venter gray yellow with gray black median stripe. Spinnerets gray black.

Prosoma (
Fig. 10
). Carapace longer than wide, with several black setae anteriorly. Both the eye rows recurved from dorsal view. Eye measurements: AME 0.08 , ALE 0.08 , PME 0.09 , PLE 0.08 ; AME–AME 0.08 , AME–ALE 0.03 , ALE–ALE 0.39 , PME–PME 0.08 , PME–PLE 0.07 , PLE–PLE 0.41 , ALE and PLE contiguous. MOA long 0.21 , front width 0.22 , back width 0.21 . Clypeus height 0.14 and covered with few setae. Promargin of chelicerae with three teeth, with the third one largest; retromargin with five small teeth. Anterior margin of endites armed with gray scopula. Labium 0.10 long, 0.18 . Sternum 0.54 long, 0.50 wide and covered with sparse black setae, with anterior lightly procurved margin.

Opisthosoma (
Fig. 10
). Oval, longer than wide, covered with sparse black setae.

Male palp (
Figs 11–12
). Embolus short, thin, curved and originating from the ventral genital bulb; median apophysis and tegular apophysis large; conductor membranous. The width of tibia equal to its length.
